this how-to guide will walk you through the steps to embed portfolium entries directly into canvas. this will allow your students to view portfolium projects and examples from within the canvas interface.inside of your canvas class module, create a newunderon the left side of the screen.on thepage, click thebutton.enter a title for your page, for example:then click on.copy the html code below (including the < and > symbols):<iframe width=350 height=750 async src=?utm=canvas></iframe>paste this html code into thewindow within canvassmodule.copy the portfolio entry url from portfolium and paste into the html window, replacing where it says(including the brackets).then click.phone:408-924-2337email:ecampus@sjsu.edulocation: irc, room 206ecampus, irc206instructional resource centersan jose state universityone washington squaresan jose, ca 95192-0026